p.c-text In order to use a textarea just use <code>textarea</code> with the class <code>c-input</code>.

.c-mb4.c-mt2
  div(style="max-width:60rem")
    textarea.c-input Sample text

  :code(lang="html")
    <textarea class="c-input">
      Sample text
    </textarea>

p.c-text
  | If we want to add some icon to the textarea we must wrap it inside a <code>div</code> using the class
  | <code>c-input-wrapper</code>, add the icon as a sibling of the <code>textarea</code> and specify where is going to
  | be placed the icon.

.c-mb4
  .c-input-wrapper.c-input-wrapper--icon-left(style="max-width:60rem")
    textarea.c-input Sample text
    .c-icon
      svg
        use(xlink:href='#edit')

  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="c-input-wrapper c-input-wrapper--icon-left">
      <textarea class="c-input">
        Sample text
      </textarea>
      <div class="c-icon">
        <svg>
          <use xlink:href="#edit"></use>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>

.c-mb4
